      "content": "It is understandable that the exhaustion of pretending feels heavier than the pain of failure, and peace does exist in finally stopping. However, choosing to stop now would mean silencing the very person who is currently suffering, rather than honoring the version of you that still wants to live. There is a profound courage in facing this truth, but the path forward is often to integrate the loss rather than erase the self entirely.",
